# modelguild.conf.example — copy to modelguild/modelguild.conf.local (git-ignored) to set your
# persistent ModelGuild preferences, or run /guild:configure, which writes it
# for you. Simple KEY=value lines; `#` starts a comment; this file is NOT executed.
#
# Why a file and not environment variables: this tool is driven by Claude Code, whose
# shell runs each command in a subshell — so a setup command can't `export` a value
# into your interactive shell and have it persist. A git-ignored file can. The env
# vars still work as one-off overrides (precedence: explicit arg > env > this file).
#
# Values here are read by the guild MCP tools (GUILD_MODEL for single-model calls,
# GUILD_MODELS for the panel). Model policy (deny/ask/allow) lives separately in
# $GUILD_POLICY when set, otherwise a ruleful modelguild/models.policy.local,
# otherwise committed modelguild/models.policy. See /guild:configure.

# Default model for /guild:consult (and any single-model call). Prefer a NON-Claude model
# so a second opinion is genuinely independent.
# GUILD_MODEL=openai/gpt-5

# Default panel for /guild:panel: 2-3 ordered ids from DIFFERENT providers (space- or
# comma-separated). guild_panel warns if the set isn't cross-provider.
# GUILD_MODELS=openai/gpt-5 google/gemini-2.5-pro

# Per-model-turn HTTP timeout in milliseconds. Default 900000 (15 min). RAISE this when a
# heavy task on a slow reasoning model legitimately runs long and aborts with "operation
# was aborted due to timeout" — e.g. a whole-repo review or a long planning session. Only
# the model-turn call uses it; the fast control-plane calls keep their own short timeout.
# Must be a positive number of milliseconds; 0/negative/non-numeric falls back to the
# default (there is no "disable timeout" — a hung turn must eventually abort). Capped at
# 2147483647 (2^31-1), Node's timer ceiling — a larger value would abort every turn instantly.
# Set it to the literal `max` to use that ceiling (~24.8 days, "effectively never abort");
# the trade-off is a genuinely hung turn then blocks until then. This sets the DEFAULT; the
# calling agent can also override it per call via each tool's `timeoutMs` input (which wins).
# GUILD_MESSAGE_TIMEOUT_MS=1800000

# Where the guild tools look for the guild-* agent DEFS when deciding whether to refuse
# a call whose hardened def is missing. Default: the .opencode/agent of the project the
# MCP server was spawned from (GUILD_PROJECT_DIR, else the CWD). NOTE: this governs ONLY
# the tool's refusal decision — opencode resolves --agent independently from its own
# config, so this MUST point at the SAME directory the defs were actually installed to.
# GUILD_AGENT_DIR=~/.config/opencode/agent

# The guild root (where the policy/config/logs live). Resolved as $GUILD_ROOT, else
# <cwd>/modelguild/, else ~/.claude/modelguild/. Set this only for a non-standard layout.
# GUILD_ROOT=/path/to/modelguild

# --- Evidence layer (src/log.ts) ------------------------------------------------
# Every model call is recorded to the git-ignored modelguild/logs/<run_id>/calls.jsonl:
# raw prompts and responses, with `expected-call`, `started`, and `completed`
# lifecycle entries sharing one call_id. These are the RECEIPTS of every exchange —
# the other model's actual words, on disk and yours to read — so logging is on by default.
# GUILD_LOG=off                  # stop recording entirely
# GUILD_LOG_DIR=/custom/path     # override the log root (disables partitioning below)
# GUILD_LOG_PROMPTS=full         # full | hash | off — what to keep of the prompt
#                                 # Claude SENT. Default `full`: the brief Claude
#                                 # wrote is itself prime audit material. But it
#                                 # means the log holds whatever repo context was
#                                 # pasted in — use `hash` (digest only, proves the
#                                 # prompt didn't change) or `off` on sensitive work.
#                                 # Responses are ALWAYS kept in full: they are the
#                                 # evidence, and they're the other model's words.
# GUILD_LOG_RETENTION_DAYS=14    # prune runs older than this; 0 disables pruning
# GUILD_LOG_PARTITION=1          # opt-in (default OFF). Narrow the log root to a
#                                 # per-project subdir BELOW the base logs tree:
#                                 # <base>/<project-key>/<run>, keyed by the CWD's git
#                                 # top-level (else the CWD). Keeps each project's runs,
#                                 # `latest` symlink, and retention separate under a
#                                 # single shared install. DISABLED when GUILD_LOG_DIR
#                                 # is explicitly set (an explicit dir wins). For a
#                                 # NON-repo project the key uses $PWD (logical), so
#                                 # entering the same dir via different symlink paths
#                                 # yields two buckets — bounded, not corruption.
